Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

When boiling, stir the @macaroni{180%g} into the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the macaroni cooks, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef and pork mince{240%g}. Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic and @mixed herbs{1%sachet} to the mince and fry, ~{1%minute}.

Next, stir in the @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @tomato passata{1%carton}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{75%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and @water{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir to combine, then set your cheesy sauce aside.

Once the mince has thickened, taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash more water if it's a little too thick.

Stir in the cooked macaroni, then transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Spoon the cheesy sauce evenly over the macaroni mixture, then sprinkle over the cheese. Pop under the grill until golden and bubbling, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the Bolognese mac and cheese is ready, share it between your plates.

Serve the @wild rocket{20%g} alongside and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!